post_text:
Attention CJU45 and families!

Information re Glenwood Show Choir Competition:

We have secured 2 charter buses for our trip. We will depart around 5am. I will confirm the departure time on Monday, Jan 27. Our performance time is 10:50am. Final awards will be at 8:55pm.

I want to thank the Fine Arts Connection helping us get the charter buses set up. We will need to raise roughly $2500 for the buses. We are planning a few fundraisers to generate the $2500. More to come soon.

BUT, we do have the following fundraising opportunity to help raise money for the charter buses - Carver Concessions (Men’s BB vs Wisconsin) this Monday, Jan 27. We would need 6 students (age 16+) and 2 adults. Guaranteed minimum of $100 per person! That would be $800!!

Report time is 5:00pm for the 7:30pm game. Please send me a message if you are interested. Thank you!!

post_text:
West Branch Fine Arts Connection is seeking your support! Each year the FAC supports the various groups financially by paying for the following: choreography, licensing fees, clinicians, Adventureland trip for middle school, instruments, stands, and so much more! Please consider donating to our students and supporting WB fine arts programs!

Currently we are trying a new fundraiser! It is called Pick a Number! Students have a numberboard with the numbers 1-20. Friends and family can "pick a number" to donate that amount. Once someone picks a number, that number is taken off the board (or X'ed out). Students are racing to get their boards completed! Multiple boxes can be crossed off with 1 donation, or boxes can be marked off with 20 different donations! Please consider supporting the WBCSD Fine Arts Programs and find a student with a Numberboard and Pick A Number!

If you would like to participate please PM the FAC and we will get you a board!

post_text:
WB Show Choir (7-12) Parade of Homes 2017
Show Choir POH sign up.

Easiest fundraiser and one of the most lucrative of the year, folks!!! We would appreciate you taking a couple hours of these days to sit in one of the areas most 'tricked-out', new and remodeled homes that will be on "Parade" from the Iowa City Area Home Builders Association to the general public. It's just that simple. Parade attendees will have tickets that will need to be punched at each location. Some folks may need to purchase their tickets at the home. That's all you have to do. That's all. That's it. It is a VERY easy way to volunteer just a couple hours at a time to raise much needed money for high school AND middle school West Branch Show Choir Programs! This is an opportunity that we have been graciously offered and we need YOU to make it a $ucce$$! (Students under the age of 15 must be accompanied by an adult)

Please use the link below to sign you and/or your child(ren) up who are involved in show choir. Thank YOU!!

http://www.signupgenius.com/go/5080f48a5a822a3f85-parade
